headline: Senate control hinges on dual Georgia runoff elections

utterances.speaker: JESSE WATTERS, FOX NEWS HOST
utterances.sentences: Hello, everybody. I'm Jesse Watters, along with Dagen McDowell, Juan Williams, Kennedy, and Greg Gutfeld. It's five o'clock in New York City, and this is The Five. President Trump speaking publicly for the first time in a week. And giving a very important update on Operation Warp Speed from the Rose Garden moments ago. Revealing when a vaccine could be available.

utterances.speaker: DONALD TRUMP, PRESIDENT OF THE UNITED STATES
utterances.sentences: Operation Warp Speed is unequaled and unrivaled anywhere in the world. Pfizer said it wasn't part of Warp Speed, but that turned out to be an unfortunate misrepresentation.  They are part, that's why we gave them the $1.95 million -- billion dollars. We will work to secure an emergency use authorization, which should be coming down extremely soon, and my administration will then coordinate the distribution of the vaccine, and it will be approved, I think again, it will be approved very, very quickly.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: The president also saying other vaccines in addition to Pfizer's could be ready soon, and while Joe Biden's team has discussed the possibility of future lockdowns, President Trump said that won't happen on his watch.

utterances.speaker: TRUMP
utterances.sentences: I will not go. This administration will not be going through a locked down. Hopefully the -- whatever happens in the future, who knows which administration will be? I guess time will tell, but I can tell you this administration will not go to a lockdown.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: All right, Dagen, a lot of good news from the update from Operation Warp Speed. I guess this was developed five times faster than any other vaccine, and they could get 20 million doses out by December, and the rest of the country could see distribution by April.

utterances.speaker: DAGEN MCDOWELL, FOX NEWS HOST
utterances.sentences: Right. President Trump knew from day one that the only way for this nation to get out of this pandemic, and he did call it the China virus in that press -- in that speech, was to, as fast as possible to get a vaccine under development, and that's part of what Operation Warp Speed has done, is dedicating billions of dollars to the development of those vaccines, but also securing that the manufacturing and the supplies of those very vaccines, that was he's talking about with Pfizer. So, you got four they are in stage three trials. Pfizer, Moderna is right on deck as well, along with AstraZeneca and Johnson & Johnson. And he also, rightfully so, took a shot at Governor Cuomo.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: I think we have some of that sound. Let's play that. And then Greg Gutfeld, Cuomo's best friend can react.

utterances.speaker: TRUMP
utterances.sentences: As soon as April, the vaccine will be available to the entire general population with the exception of places like New York state where for political reasons, the governor, he doesn't trust the fact that it's this White House, this administration. So, we won't be delivering it to New York until we have authorization to do so and that pains me to say that. So, the governor, Governor Cuomo will have to let us know when he is ready for it.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: I'm sorry, Dagen, you wanted to get in there.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.sentences: Well, this -- this has been the best example of a public/private partnership that President Trump put in place. But Governor Cuomo, he has to do his own safety review of the vaccine because, we can't trust Donald Trump's FDA, which is ludicrous and shows a complete lack of knowledge about the way that vaccine trials happen with independents safety review board.  But also, he said recently that he and other governors will potentially stop the vaccine distribution before it does damage. So, he killed thousands of elderly people because of his nursing home order, so he's trying to up the total of the number of people that he kills. He is an ego with a haircut that could potentially kill you. That's who the governor is.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: I think it's got to be posturing from Cuomo, Greg. I don't see there's anyway where 49 states take distribution and he says, no, no, slow it down, we're not ready yet.

utterances.speaker: GREG GUTFELD, FOX NEWS HOST
utterances.sentences: Yes, I think you're right. I think you're right. I just have to point out that this is kind of a big deal. I was in this past life, I was a health journalist, I don't recall this ever happening in my life where you did something so fast and it ss so promising so quickly, with whatever system that was created here you can employ and target other illnesses.   We still don't obviously have a vaccine for AIDS. There are other diseases that we could -- we could tackle with this and I think you can't -- I don't think you can underplay this. I have a terrible analogy for the vaccine and Joe Biden.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Go ahead.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: He basically inherited a housebroken pet. He didn't have to do the work for this. So, he may reap the benefits of having a great vaccine, but he never really had to put the work in.  It's like when somebody marries somebody who is recently divorced. Maybe all the habits have been worked out, you know? And that's it. But the thing is, and I just want to focus on what Trump said about the lockdowns -- sorry.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Go ahead.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: He is right. You don't want to be in the prison of two ideas of no lockdown versus lockdown, you want an adjustable path. But we do know that people with less occupational freedom have higher stress levels, we are seeing this in suicide rates so we have to -- we can't just stare at one variable, which is deaths. We have to look at all the variables from zero to 25. I believe we have had a total, in age, we've had a total of 500 deaths. So, we -- meanwhile, I guess like 65 and over it's about 180,000, 150,000, somewhere around there. So, we have to be able to adjust and be realistic about this and I think he is -- he is correct to factor in the damage that it's happening on people who don't necessarily have to be locked down.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Well someone else housebroke rookie.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: And it wasn't Emma and I and we're very grateful for that, so Joe Biden obviously is going to be very happy. So yes, he -- Joe Biden --

utterances.speaker: LISA KENNEDY MONTGOMERY, FOX NEWS HOST
utterances.sentences: Emma received two housebroken, that's wonderful.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: I still have some days. But he will be inheriting --

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Operation Warp Speed and not just Operation Warp Speed, you'll have full distribution probably churning if everything breaks Biden's way with the certification by the time he gets in there.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: Yes. And that's one of the issues, the supply chain because for these first two vaccines that will be ready, you know, of course we've heard so much about the Pfizer vaccine, it has to be stored at 94 degrees below zero and there aren't trucks that cold, and there aren't freezers that cold even in major cities with big hospitals. So that's why you look at a couple companies down the road, Johnson & Johnson had some more promising vaccine and that it doesn't have to be stored as cold, it can be stored longer and you only, at this point it's possible you could only need one dose of the Johnson & Johnson vaccine, but they are a few months behind the rest of them. But I may wait for that one.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Yes, who don't like needles are very happy about it.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: But I have to say, and Dagen knows this intimately, when you have a loved one who is going to or struggle with cancer and you are reading and consuming as much information as you possibly can about a potential treatment.  And if we can get the FDA out of the way and, you know, really impose some of the right to try stuff that the president pushed so hard, you could see a groundbreaking new horizon in medicine with therapies that can be ready, faster especially if people with, you know, right to try conditions, if they're willing to take them. So, part of this is very, very exciting. Take the politics out of it so you can keep people alive.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: I hope they do. And Juan, you'll be getting vaccinated, right?

utterances.speaker: JUAN WILLIAMS, FOX NEWS HOST
utterances.sentences: Yes. Well, I would take them the minute -- you know, I'm in the older age groups, so I really, you know, I worry about this virus. But I must say I have a different take than what I've been hearing here because to me, one, I don't think the development of the vaccine was related to Operation Warp Speed. It was a separate commercial free market enterprise, let's salute that, done by Pfizer and a German company.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Didn't they get money from the government?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: No, they did not.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.sentences: They got --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: They got a whole pool of money.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: No.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.sentences: They ink a deal -- they ink a deal with Health and Human Services, there is a deal on Pfizer's web site, that they got two -- almost  $2 billion for manufacturing and distribution and they say in the press release, as part of Operation Warp Speed's --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: Right but it wasn't --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Right.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.sentences: -- goal of 300 vaccines.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: We'll send you the --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: OK. It wasn't part of --

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.sentences: Three hundred million does.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: OK. But my point is for the last week since the election, President Trump has been moping around. This is the first time we've seen him, as you said, and he hasn't been dealing with this issue. So, but to my  --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: What issue?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: COVID. So, to my mind --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: That's a press conference about the vaccines.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: Excuse me, I just said, we haven't seen him for which it is the first time.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Now you miss him, Juan. Now you miss him.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: So again, OK.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: That's sad.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: So, here's the reality, that he's leaving us with what people I think are calling a hot mess on Joe Biden's doorstep. This is not a trained puppy, this is something out of control that's raging in our country and we are not just talking about attacks on the governor of New York or saying whatever happens in terms of the election, which was the message he delivered there. We're talking about a nation that is right now, Thursday we had 150,000 new cases, the highest since the pandemic began. We had 66,000 people in hospitals, a record number. More than 1,000 dead, eight of the last 12 days since the start of this month. So, when we come to thinking about how we deal with this, his focus is on we're never going to have a lockdown not in this administration. We don't know what's to come again. Not acknowledging that he lost the election.  But the reality is that Joe Biden has said that he is listening to Dr. Fauci who says he doesn't think that a lockdown is necessary at this moment. We had a press conference today from the man who is leading Joe Biden's task force, he said we don't need a lockdown right now. What we need to do are take specific steps, including the masks, the hand washing, the distancing.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.sentences: Can I add, Juan.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: That is the reality of what's going on.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: So, it's the same thing as the Trump task force?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: No, it is not --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Yes, it is.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: -- because obviously, they are paying attention. They understand our nation right now is facing a crisis.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: Juan, you have to ask two people who are consulting President-elect Biden right now, Michael Osterholm who has called for a lockdown and Ezekiel Emanuel who hates people over 75 and doesn't think that old people who are the ones who are dying from the virus, he doesn't think that they should be the priority to get the vaccine!

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.sentences: Can I add one thing?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: No but the point is, that what you have is people pointing out different ideas.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: That's a big point, Juan.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: But, no. Fauci --

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: I love people over 75.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: Hang on, hang on. I'm glad you do, but I'm saying Fauci and the head of the task force have been very clear. There's no need to fight about this lockdown because both sides say right now, that's not where we are.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: That's not what you said but go ahead.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.sentences: I observed case fatality ratio in the United States --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.sentences: -- is lower than it was in recent weeks because I've got the data from Johns Hopkins, 2.3 percent --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Exactly.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.sentences: -- in the United States, lower than Mexico, Iran, Italy, United Kingdom, Columbia, Brazil, Spain, Turkey, Argentina, Belgium, Romania. We're right on par with France, number one. Number two.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: yes. I'll tell you what.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.sentences: About the vaccine.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: I thought you were so concerned about Americans, Dagen.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.sentences: About the vaccine.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: And so now you want to talk about everything but what's going on in our country.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.sentences: No, I'll talk --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: Because you want to use that to defend Trump.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.sentences: Let me finish. Let me finish.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: No, no, no. Can I --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: What she's trying to point out is what I keep saying every day on the show that you avoid that the percentage -- the fatality rate is declining. Right now, it's about 2.3 to 2.4 percent. A month ago, it was 2.7. October, it's like 3 percent. In June, 5.5, April, 5.9. I hate going through these numbers because, but we have to because you are spreading lies, Juan.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: No, because you say --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: And you got to stop.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: -- you say stuff like --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: It's going down.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: -- the only reason that we have more reports of coronavirus is because of an increase in testing.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: No, I didn't say that.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: That's not right, Greg.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: One of the reasons we have more cases --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: that's not right.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: One of the reasons why we have cases is because we're testing.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: No.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: I didn't say the only --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: No, but that's not true. Because Greg, we have right now --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Yes, it's true.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: Greg, we have more testing and we have a record number of cases.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: The rate is declining.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: So, there is more testing.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: The percent --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: No, it's not.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Yes, it is.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: All right. OK, Juan, Juan, for the record, because I just looked at this earlier today --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: Yes, go ahead.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: The media cannot report science.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: At the end of September we were testing on average 800,000 a day. Now, we are testing 1.6 million a day.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: We should be testing more.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: We have doubled the testing in one month.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: Good.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: We have doubled the testing in one month and that's a fact. Coming up, Barack Obama is attacking President Trump over the election, claiming he is dangerous for democracy.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: The fight over the election continuing. The Associated Press projecting today that President Trump will win North Carolina. A hand recount is starting in Georgia while the president's lawyers are launching new challenges in Pennsylvania. And now former President Obama is going after President Trump and Republicans for challenging the results.

utterances.speaker: BARACK OBAMA, FORMER PRESIDENT OF THE UNITED STATES
utterances.sentences: I'm more troubled by the fact that other Republican officials who clearly know better are going along with this, are humoring him in this fashion. It is one more step in delegitimizing not just the incoming Biden administration, but democracy generally. And that's a dangerous path.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: Jesse, the Trump team today lost their third effort to delay certification in Michigan. They pulled out of an Arizona challenge. Why are they unable to show evidence in court of any fraud or corruption in this election if they keep saying there is?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Well, that didn't have to do anything to do with fraud, those cases. If you look at the affidavits there's dozens of them and they talk about suspicious ballot dumping, forged signatures, all kinds of mischievous activity. And if a third of those allegations are accurate that means there is more evidence of corruption in this election than there was evidence of collusion in the last election.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: I'm just saying we haven't seen any in court?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Well, Juan, it takes a little while to go to court, present your evidence and have a case built. Because this isn't going to happen overnight. This is something that you have to have confidence in the election. You can't just have Democrats thinking the election was kosher. You want the rest of the country to believe that too. And until you go out and follow up on these allegations, every single election going forward if you use mail ballots to this level, people are going to be suspicious about and you don't want that and I don't want that.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: Well, so, Greg.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: The Department of Homeland Security said the election this year was the safest, most secure ever. Why won't Trump accept what his own department is saying?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Wait, I have something -- the decision desk just called North Carolina for Joe Biden in 2024.

utterances.speaker: MONGTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: Exciting.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Yes. Yes. Amazing. The Department of Homeland Security could be right, but that's compared to what? I mean, when you have Joe Biden's future, whatever, chief of staff saying that everything is fixed and you can't be calling people crazy for being suspicious of this election when people for four years said that Trump was an existential threat to the world. If he is an existential threat, then you are going to do everything you can to undermine it. By the way, America has done regime changes for less. I mean, if you ask the left -- not the left because the left are actually closer to the centrists than the never-Trumpers, if you ask the never- Trumps who's worse, Iran in the 1950s or Trump in 2017, they would say Trump 2017. So, they actually have a reason, a reason to fix an election. And everybody, everybody has reason to be suspicious of this. And to marginalize people who don't buy this, that's part of the game, to make you feel stupid for believing this is not for it. And by the way, Obama is also saying the reason Trump won in 2016 was because of racism. Yes, millions of Americans who voted for Obama also voted for Trump and that's because they are racist? I -- you know, people always thought that he didn't like America. No, he just didn't like Americans.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: All right. So, Kennedy, is Trump jeopardizing our national security by not allowing Joe Biden to see the national security briefing? An increasing number of Republican senators are saying look, I don't care what you want to say, give him the national security briefing.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: No, and Lindsey Graham has said the same thing. I'm very confident that Joe Biden has been around the federal government for long enough that he has deep-staters who are whispering in his ear. And he was vice president four years ago so I'm pretty certain that he has a good, running knowledge. He may have forgotten some of it, what the global landscape is like. And you know, he'll get the briefing books. I'm very, very confident in that. But I'm also confident, and the thing that frustrates me is, if Democrats are willing to sign a pledge and say that we will never contest an election again, we will never contest a close election again because it's so childish, then I think I will put a lot of people's minds at ease. I don't think they're going to because if you lose a close election you were going to contest the results in one way or another. I don't think we are going to have anything but close presidential contests for the foreseeable future.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: But you know that this one wasn't that close, right?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: In a lot of states it was close.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: In Wisconsin it most certainly was.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: No, no, I'm saying --

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: No, I know how the Electoral College work. I understand that.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Where it mattered. It was close.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: You know how the Electoral College, OK.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: I also know what the polling was. I mean, the polling --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: Yes. But the polling was, but right now Joe Biden not only leads in the -- he leads in the popular vote. He leads strong in the Electoral College.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: That doesn't matter.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Juan, you know the polls were wrong.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: OK.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: In California, Trump won. I mean, it's a stupid -- it's a stupid argument is my point.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: OK.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Maybe we should remove California.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: Polling I'm just saying --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: In California lots of voters --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: -- popular votes, Electoral College all went one direction.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: No, I understand that.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: OK.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: Juan, I have not disputed that but why did Democrats sent teams of lawyers to places like Florida ready to contest the results if Joe Biden only lost by half a point --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Big point.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: -- in Florida? They were going to do the exact same thing. And I talked to Democrats the week before the election who said they are trying to steal this from us. That was Democrats, so they were ready to do the whole thing. So, if they're going to call it off and not do this when the tides of fortune are reversed, then I got it.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: All right. All right. So, Dagen, you know, I was thinking about why Republicans are refusing to tell President Trump that he lost. And I've got to think, are they just worried about hurting his feelings? Is he like a snowflake on the right?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Like Hillary?

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: She won.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.sentences: Because the rate -- because there is clearly fishy things going on with the vote.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: Like what?

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.sentences: So, the biggest -- well, I mean, you can read the affidavits that have been filed in this case.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: But we are two weeks out.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.sentences: Listen. Let me -- let me -- I didn't -- I didn't --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: Put it before a court.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.sentences: I didn't use the word fraud, but we had an unprecedented number of mail-in ballots and I can tell you in New York City, I got somebody else's ballot, absentee ballot application in my mailbox. So, to take a few weeks to make sure and convince the American population that the election was fair, you would want that for Joe Biden and Kamala Harris, number one. Number two, I might listen to President Obama if once in four years he had stepped up and said this Russia collusion thing, it's not going anywhere. It's a bunch of lies, you need to accept Trump as your president. GUTFELD; Right.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.sentences: He's angry, he doesn't believe in democracy because he can't believe that President Trump never got elected after he was in office for eight years. You know why? Because the Obama-Biden economy sucked to high heaven. People's wages in this country never even grew at 3 percent, and people, the working-class Americans weren't getting ahead. That's why President Trump got elected, and one more thing, I've got a couple of (Inaudible) we can get to work and saw California off and push it into the Pacific. So, get ready.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: Be Trump property --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: I just wish somebody would be honest with the president. Coming up next, the fight for the Senate. It comes down to Georgia. Will some of the rhetoric from progressive Democrats hurt the party? Next on The Five.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL

utterances.speaker: JESSE WATTERS, FOX NEWS HOST
utterances.utterance: Hello, everybody. I'm Jesse Watters, along with Dagen McDowell, Juan Williams, Kennedy, and Greg Gutfeld. It's five o'clock in New York City, and this is The Five. President Trump speaking publicly for the first time in a week. And giving a very important update on Operation Warp Speed from the Rose Garden moments ago. Revealing when a vaccine could be available.

utterances.speaker: DONALD TRUMP, PRESIDENT OF THE UNITED STATES
utterances.utterance: Operation Warp Speed is unequaled and unrivaled anywhere in the world. Pfizer said it wasn't part of Warp Speed, but that turned out to be an unfortunate misrepresentation. They are part, that's why we gave them the $1.95 million -- billion dollars. We will work to secure an emergency use authorization, which should be coming down extremely soon, and my administration will then coordinate the distribution of the vaccine, and it will be approved, I think again, it will be approved very, very quickly.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: The president also saying other vaccines in addition to Pfizer's could be ready soon, and while Joe Biden's team has discussed the possibility of future lockdowns, President Trump said that won't happen on his watch.

utterances.speaker: TRUMP
utterances.utterance: I will not go. This administration will not be going through a locked down. Hopefully the -- whatever happens in the future, who knows which administration will be? I guess time will tell, but I can tell you this administration will not go to a lockdown.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: All right, Dagen, a lot of good news from the update from Operation Warp Speed. I guess this was developed five times faster than any other vaccine, and they could get 20 million doses out by December, and the rest of the country could see distribution by April.

utterances.speaker: DAGEN MCDOWELL, FOX NEWS HOST
utterances.utterance: Right. President Trump knew from day one that the only way for this nation to get out of this pandemic, and he did call it the China virus in that press -- in that speech, was to, as fast as possible to get a vaccine under development, and that's part of what Operation Warp Speed has done, is dedicating billions of dollars to the development of those vaccines, but also securing that the manufacturing and the supplies of those very vaccines, that was he's talking about with Pfizer. So, you got four they are in stage three trials. Pfizer, Moderna is right on deck as well, along with AstraZeneca and Johnson & Johnson. And he also, rightfully so, took a shot at Governor Cuomo.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: I think we have some of that sound. Let's play that. And then Greg Gutfeld, Cuomo's best friend can react.

utterances.speaker: TRUMP
utterances.utterance: As soon as April, the vaccine will be available to the entire general population with the exception of places like New York state where for political reasons, the governor, he doesn't trust the fact that it's this White House, this administration. So, we won't be delivering it to New York until we have authorization to do so and that pains me to say that. So, the governor, Governor Cuomo will have to let us know when he is ready for it.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: I'm sorry, Dagen, you wanted to get in there.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: Well, this -- this has been the best example of a public/private partnership that President Trump put in place. But Governor Cuomo, he has to do his own safety review of the vaccine because, we can't trust Donald Trump's FDA, which is ludicrous and shows a complete lack of knowledge about the way that vaccine trials happen with independents safety review board. But also, he said recently that he and other governors will potentially stop the vaccine distribution before it does damage. So, he killed thousands of elderly people because of his nursing home order, so he's trying to up the total of the number of people that he kills. He is an ego with a haircut that could potentially kill you. That's who the governor is.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: I think it's got to be posturing from Cuomo, Greg. I don't see there's anyway where 49 states take distribution and he says, no, no, slow it down, we're not ready yet.

utterances.speaker: GREG GUTFELD, FOX NEWS HOST
utterances.utterance: Yes, I think you're right. I think you're right. I just have to point out that this is kind of a big deal. I was in this past life, I was a health journalist, I don't recall this ever happening in my life where you did something so fast and it ss so promising so quickly, with whatever system that was created here you can employ and target other illnesses. We still don't obviously have a vaccine for AIDS. There are other diseases that we could -- we could tackle with this and I think you can't -- I don't think you can underplay this. I have a terrible analogy for the vaccine and Joe Biden.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Go ahead.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: He basically inherited a housebroken pet. He didn't have to do the work for this. So, he may reap the benefits of having a great vaccine, but he never really had to put the work in. It's like when somebody marries somebody who is recently divorced. Maybe all the habits have been worked out, you know? And that's it. But the thing is, and I just want to focus on what Trump said about the lockdowns -- sorry.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Go ahead.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: He is right. You don't want to be in the prison of two ideas of no lockdown versus lockdown, you want an adjustable path. But we do know that people with less occupational freedom have higher stress levels, we are seeing this in suicide rates so we have to -- we can't just stare at one variable, which is deaths. We have to look at all the variables from zero to 25. I believe we have had a total, in age, we've had a total of 500 deaths. So, we -- meanwhile, I guess like 65 and over it's about 180,000, 150,000, somewhere around there. So, we have to be able to adjust and be realistic about this and I think he is -- he is correct to factor in the damage that it's happening on people who don't necessarily have to be locked down.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Well someone else housebroke rookie.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: And it wasn't Emma and I and we're very grateful for that, so Joe Biden obviously is going to be very happy. So yes, he -- Joe Biden --

utterances.speaker: LISA KENNEDY MONTGOMERY, FOX NEWS HOST
utterances.utterance: Emma received two housebroken, that's wonderful.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: I still have some days. But he will be inheriting --

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Operation Warp Speed and not just Operation Warp Speed, you'll have full distribution probably churning if everything breaks Biden's way with the certification by the time he gets in there.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: Yes. And that's one of the issues, the supply chain because for these first two vaccines that will be ready, you know, of course we've heard so much about the Pfizer vaccine, it has to be stored at 94 degrees below zero and there aren't trucks that cold, and there aren't freezers that cold even in major cities with big hospitals. So that's why you look at a couple companies down the road, Johnson & Johnson had some more promising vaccine and that it doesn't have to be stored as cold, it can be stored longer and you only, at this point it's possible you could only need one dose of the Johnson & Johnson vaccine, but they are a few months behind the rest of them. But I may wait for that one.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Yes, who don't like needles are very happy about it.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: But I have to say, and Dagen knows this intimately, when you have a loved one who is going to or struggle with cancer and you are reading and consuming as much information as you possibly can about a potential treatment. And if we can get the FDA out of the way and, you know, really impose some of the right to try stuff that the president pushed so hard, you could see a groundbreaking new horizon in medicine with therapies that can be ready, faster especially if people with, you know, right to try conditions, if they're willing to take them. So, part of this is very, very exciting. Take the politics out of it so you can keep people alive.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: I hope they do. And Juan, you'll be getting vaccinated, right?

utterances.speaker: JUAN WILLIAMS, FOX NEWS HOST
utterances.utterance: Yes. Well, I would take them the minute -- you know, I'm in the older age groups, so I really, you know, I worry about this virus. But I must say I have a different take than what I've been hearing here because to me, one, I don't think the development of the vaccine was related to Operation Warp Speed. It was a separate commercial free market enterprise, let's salute that, done by Pfizer and a German company.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Didn't they get money from the government?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: No, they did not.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: They got --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: They got a whole pool of money.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: No.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: They ink a deal -- they ink a deal with Health and Human Services, there is a deal on Pfizer's web site, that they got two -- almost $2 billion for manufacturing and distribution and they say in the press release, as part of Operation Warp Speed's --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Right but it wasn't --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Right.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: -- goal of 300 vaccines.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: We'll send you the --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: OK. It wasn't part of --

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: Three hundred million does.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: OK. But my point is for the last week since the election, President Trump has been moping around. This is the first time we've seen him, as you said, and he hasn't been dealing with this issue. So, but to my --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: What issue?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: COVID. So, to my mind --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: That's a press conference about the vaccines.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Excuse me, I just said, we haven't seen him for which it is the first time.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Now you miss him, Juan. Now you miss him.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: So again, OK.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: That's sad.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: So, here's the reality, that he's leaving us with what people I think are calling a hot mess on Joe Biden's doorstep. This is not a trained puppy, this is something out of control that's raging in our country and we are not just talking about attacks on the governor of New York or saying whatever happens in terms of the election, which was the message he delivered there. We're talking about a nation that is right now, Thursday we had 150,000 new cases, the highest since the pandemic began. We had 66,000 people in hospitals, a record number. More than 1,000 dead, eight of the last 12 days since the start of this month. So, when we come to thinking about how we deal with this, his focus is on we're never going to have a lockdown not in this administration. We don't know what's to come again. Not acknowledging that he lost the election. But the reality is that Joe Biden has said that he is listening to Dr. Fauci who says he doesn't think that a lockdown is necessary at this moment. We had a press conference today from the man who is leading Joe Biden's task force, he said we don't need a lockdown right now. What we need to do are take specific steps, including the masks, the hand washing, the distancing.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: Can I add, Juan.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: That is the reality of what's going on.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: So, it's the same thing as the Trump task force?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: No, it is not --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Yes, it is.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: -- because obviously, they are paying attention. They understand our nation right now is facing a crisis.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: Juan, you have to ask two people who are consulting President-elect Biden right now, Michael Osterholm who has called for a lockdown and Ezekiel Emanuel who hates people over 75 and doesn't think that old people who are the ones who are dying from the virus, he doesn't think that they should be the priority to get the vaccine!

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: Can I add one thing?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: No but the point is, that what you have is people pointing out different ideas.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: That's a big point, Juan.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: But, no. Fauci --

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: I love people over 75.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Hang on, hang on. I'm glad you do, but I'm saying Fauci and the head of the task force have been very clear. There's no need to fight about this lockdown because both sides say right now, that's not where we are.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: That's not what you said but go ahead.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: I observed case fatality ratio in the United States --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: -- is lower than it was in recent weeks because I've got the data from Johns Hopkins, 2.3 percent --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Exactly.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: -- in the United States, lower than Mexico, Iran, Italy, United Kingdom, Columbia, Brazil, Spain, Turkey, Argentina, Belgium, Romania. We're right on par with France, number one. Number two.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: yes. I'll tell you what.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: About the vaccine.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: I thought you were so concerned about Americans, Dagen.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: About the vaccine.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: And so now you want to talk about everything but what's going on in our country.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: No, I'll talk --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Because you want to use that to defend Trump.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: Let me finish. Let me finish.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: No, no, no. Can I --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: What she's trying to point out is what I keep saying every day on the show that you avoid that the percentage -- the fatality rate is declining. Right now, it's about 2.3 to 2.4 percent. A month ago, it was 2.7. October, it's like 3 percent. In June, 5.5, April, 5.9. I hate going through these numbers because, but we have to because you are spreading lies, Juan.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: No, because you say --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: And you got to stop.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: -- you say stuff like --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: It's going down.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: -- the only reason that we have more reports of coronavirus is because of an increase in testing.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: No, I didn't say that.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: That's not right, Greg.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: One of the reasons we have more cases --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: that's not right.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: One of the reasons why we have cases is because we're testing.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: No.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I didn't say the only --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: No, but that's not true. Because Greg, we have right now --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes, it's true.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Greg, we have more testing and we have a record number of cases.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: The rate is declining.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: So, there is more testing.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: The percent --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: No, it's not.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes, it is.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: All right. OK, Juan, Juan, for the record, because I just looked at this earlier today --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Yes, go ahead.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: The media cannot report science.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: At the end of September we were testing on average 800,000 a day. Now, we are testing 1.6 million a day.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: We should be testing more.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: We have doubled the testing in one month.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Good.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: We have doubled the testing in one month and that's a fact. Coming up, Barack Obama is attacking President Trump over the election, claiming he is dangerous for democracy.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: The fight over the election continuing. The Associated Press projecting today that President Trump will win North Carolina. A hand recount is starting in Georgia while the president's lawyers are launching new challenges in Pennsylvania. And now former President Obama is going after President Trump and Republicans for challenging the results.

utterances.speaker: BARACK OBAMA, FORMER PRESIDENT OF THE UNITED STATES
utterances.utterance: I'm more troubled by the fact that other Republican officials who clearly know better are going along with this, are humoring him in this fashion. It is one more step in delegitimizing not just the incoming Biden administration, but democracy generally. And that's a dangerous path.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Jesse, the Trump team today lost their third effort to delay certification in Michigan. They pulled out of an Arizona challenge. Why are they unable to show evidence in court of any fraud or corruption in this election if they keep saying there is?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Well, that didn't have to do anything to do with fraud, those cases. If you look at the affidavits there's dozens of them and they talk about suspicious ballot dumping, forged signatures, all kinds of mischievous activity. And if a third of those allegations are accurate that means there is more evidence of corruption in this election than there was evidence of collusion in the last election.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: I'm just saying we haven't seen any in court?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Well, Juan, it takes a little while to go to court, present your evidence and have a case built. Because this isn't going to happen overnight. This is something that you have to have confidence in the election. You can't just have Democrats thinking the election was kosher. You want the rest of the country to believe that too. And until you go out and follow up on these allegations, every single election going forward if you use mail ballots to this level, people are going to be suspicious about and you don't want that and I don't want that.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Well, so, Greg.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: The Department of Homeland Security said the election this year was the safest, most secure ever. Why won't Trump accept what his own department is saying?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Wait, I have something -- the decision desk just called North Carolina for Joe Biden in 2024.

utterances.speaker: MONGTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: Exciting.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes. Yes. Amazing. The Department of Homeland Security could be right, but that's compared to what? I mean, when you have Joe Biden's future, whatever, chief of staff saying that everything is fixed and you can't be calling people crazy for being suspicious of this election when people for four years said that Trump was an existential threat to the world. If he is an existential threat, then you are going to do everything you can to undermine it. By the way, America has done regime changes for less. I mean, if you ask the left -- not the left because the left are actually closer to the centrists than the never-Trumpers, if you ask the never- Trumps who's worse, Iran in the 1950s or Trump in 2017, they would say Trump 2017. So, they actually have a reason, a reason to fix an election. And everybody, everybody has reason to be suspicious of this. And to marginalize people who don't buy this, that's part of the game, to make you feel stupid for believing this is not for it. And by the way, Obama is also saying the reason Trump won in 2016 was because of racism. Yes, millions of Americans who voted for Obama also voted for Trump and that's because they are racist? I -- you know, people always thought that he didn't like America. No, he just didn't like Americans.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: All right. So, Kennedy, is Trump jeopardizing our national security by not allowing Joe Biden to see the national security briefing? An increasing number of Republican senators are saying look, I don't care what you want to say, give him the national security briefing.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: No, and Lindsey Graham has said the same thing. I'm very confident that Joe Biden has been around the federal government for long enough that he has deep-staters who are whispering in his ear. And he was vice president four years ago so I'm pretty certain that he has a good, running knowledge. He may have forgotten some of it, what the global landscape is like. And you know, he'll get the briefing books. I'm very, very confident in that. But I'm also confident, and the thing that frustrates me is, if Democrats are willing to sign a pledge and say that we will never contest an election again, we will never contest a close election again because it's so childish, then I think I will put a lot of people's minds at ease. I don't think they're going to because if you lose a close election you were going to contest the results in one way or another. I don't think we are going to have anything but close presidential contests for the foreseeable future.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: But you know that this one wasn't that close, right?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: In a lot of states it was close.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: In Wisconsin it most certainly was.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: No, no, I'm saying --

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: No, I know how the Electoral College work. I understand that.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Where it mattered. It was close.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: You know how the Electoral College, OK.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: I also know what the polling was. I mean, the polling --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Yes. But the polling was, but right now Joe Biden not only leads in the -- he leads in the popular vote. He leads strong in the Electoral College.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: That doesn't matter.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Juan, you know the polls were wrong.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: OK.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: In California, Trump won. I mean, it's a stupid -- it's a stupid argument is my point.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: OK.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Maybe we should remove California.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Polling I'm just saying --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: In California lots of voters --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: -- popular votes, Electoral College all went one direction.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: No, I understand that.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: OK.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: Juan, I have not disputed that but why did Democrats sent teams of lawyers to places like Florida ready to contest the results if Joe Biden only lost by half a point --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Big point.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: -- in Florida? They were going to do the exact same thing. And I talked to Democrats the week before the election who said they are trying to steal this from us. That was Democrats, so they were ready to do the whole thing. So, if they're going to call it off and not do this when the tides of fortune are reversed, then I got it.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: All right. All right. So, Dagen, you know, I was thinking about why Republicans are refusing to tell President Trump that he lost. And I've got to think, are they just worried about hurting his feelings? Is he like a snowflake on the right?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Like Hillary?

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: She won.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: Because the rate -- because there is clearly fishy things going on with the vote.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Like what?

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: So, the biggest -- well, I mean, you can read the affidavits that have been filed in this case.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: But we are two weeks out.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: Listen. Let me -- let me -- I didn't -- I didn't --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Put it before a court.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: I didn't use the word fraud, but we had an unprecedented number of mail-in ballots and I can tell you in New York City, I got somebody else's ballot, absentee ballot application in my mailbox. So, to take a few weeks to make sure and convince the American population that the election was fair, you would want that for Joe Biden and Kamala Harris, number one. Number two, I might listen to President Obama if once in four years he had stepped up and said this Russia collusion thing, it's not going anywhere. It's a bunch of lies, you need to accept Trump as your president. GUTFELD; Right.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: He's angry, he doesn't believe in democracy because he can't believe that President Trump never got elected after he was in office for eight years. You know why? Because the Obama-Biden economy sucked to high heaven. People's wages in this country never even grew at 3 percent, and people, the working-class Americans weren't getting ahead. That's why President Trump got elected, and one more thing, I've got a couple of (Inaudible) we can get to work and saw California off and push it into the Pacific. So, get ready.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: Be Trump property --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
